post_text:
A huge shout out and thank you to Logan and Jeremy Shelley for spending multiple hours of work so we were able to live stream the ceremony so perfectly! Also, to Mrs. Shackleford, Ms. Blossom, Mrs. Crites, Coach Martin, Mrs. Hopper, Mr. McLendon and Mr. White for your hard work in the preparation of graduation. A special thank you to Casey Denton, Jim Sixkiller, Tiffany Nash, Christine Pendry, Gina Turner and Bill Rutherford for your hard work on the bleachers and the football stadium. Thank you to Traci and Rod Odle for taking pictures, Abigail Lyons for the slide shows, and to guest speaker Wayne Thomas of Kind at Heart Ministries (Class of 1998). Thank you to anyone else who had a part in preparing for this celebration. I believe Miss Julia Haggard spoke correctly in her Valedictorian address, there is something special about this class, this school, and this community. Congratulations Class of 2020!
- Mr. Simmons
text:
A huge shout out and thank you to Logan and Jeremy Shelley for spending multiple hours of work so we were able to live stream the ceremony so perfectly! Also, to Mrs. Shackleford, Ms. Blossom, Mrs. Crites, Coach Martin, Mrs. Hopper, Mr. McLendon and Mr. White for your hard work in the preparation of graduation. A special thank you to Casey Denton, Jim Sixkiller, Tiffany Nash, Christine Pendry, Gina Turner and Bill Rutherford for your hard work on the bleachers and the football stadium. Thank you to Traci and Rod Odle for taking pictures, Abigail Lyons for the slide shows, and to guest speaker Wayne Thomas of Kind at Heart Ministries (Class of 1998). Thank you to anyone else who had a part in preparing for this celebration. I believe Miss Julia Haggard spoke correctly in her Valedictorian address, there is something special about this class, this school, and this community. Congratulations Class of 2020!
- Mr. Simmons

post_text: If your student was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

post_text: Attention Parents/Guardians and Students: The Hornets of Character After school program will begin on April 6 virtually from 3:15 - 5:30, along with sending home the activities with the packets from the school! You will need to download Google Hangouts meet to access the sessions. The daily schedule will be sent out everyday on Facebook and the school's website. All you'll need to do is click on the link next to the activity you want to join! We will have music, art, emphasis, physical education and tutoring for grades Pk-5th. We will also have an after school program for students in grades 6th-8th, the schedule and activities will be posted shortly!Any questions, please call Coach Waltman at 918-226-9565.

post_text: A sweet thank you!!! Thank you
shared_text:
Megan Hause Brueckner
March 24 at 11:57 AM ·

Picked up the kids’ free meals today! Please help out your local school by picking up meals for your kids while we are out of school. We want to keep people like our Nana employed during this time. Anyone 18 and under in your household is eligible. Just drive up to the pick up location and they will give you what you need for your family. You don’t even have to get out of your vehicle! Today’s lunch is cheeseburgers and we even received breakfast for in the morning! Thank you Colcord Schools for taking care of kiddos during this uncertain time.

post_text: Wyandotte Jr. High Powerlifting results. Hope they are all on here!! Congrats to each student!!!
text: Wyandotte Jr. High Powerlifting results. Hope they are all on here!! Congrats to each student!!!

post_text: Jr. High Powerlifting at Wyandotte Schools today. Parents and guardians I just want to congratulate you on fine kids you have raised. We have the very best. The very best. I watched as they encouraged each other and smiled as they accomplished each goal that the coaches gave them to meet. There were looks of disappointment as one’s best wasn’t good enough for a lift. I saw hope as they looked forward to the next time. Our kids need to be told how great they are! I encourage you today to tell these kids when you see them how proud of them you are. I sure am. Hornet Proud!! We will post results later. I tried to get a snap of every kid. If you don’t see yours I am sorry.
